& quot ; just enough & quot ; is more than enough ... .. `` just enough '' is more than enough : a turgid , pretentious , strident , and wholly unoriginal piece of work . its framework neither breaks any new ground in the study of the sociology of business or organization behavior , nor is it a particularly useful addition to the realm of self-help pop-business literature . at best , this might have been a reasonable ten page article in the harvard business review , but surely not enough material for 280 pages ! better to read & quot ; do what you love , the money will follow : discovering your right livelihood , & quot ; by marsha sinetar , and call it a day